main event: On March 25, 1953 at 2330Z, a civilian reported an unidentified probable sighting in Kent, England. The observation lasted 3 minutes and was of a ground-visual type, with the observed course being northwest.
interesting points: The sighting was of a clear, disc-shaped object in gray/yellow color, which changed shape and moved steadily in an oval group from south to northwest.
Another oval object disappeared to the west, and this second object was also observed by a Mr. Atte.
The report mentions ground mist and clear conditions with no reported physical evidence.
The conclusion of the observation was that it was an unidentified probable sighting.
The report was sent to various military and intelligence headquarters for further investigation.
